---
import CallToAction from '~/components/widgets/CallToAction.astro';
import Content from '~/components/widgets/Content.astro';
import Features2 from '~/components/widgets/Features2.astro';
import Hero from '~/components/widgets/Hero.astro';
import Testimonials from '~/components/widgets/Testimonials.astro';
import Layout from '~/layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import Brands from '~/components/widgets/Brands.astro';
import Features from '~/components/widgets/Features.astro';
import Button from '~/components/ui/Button.astro';

const metadata = {
  title: 'Employee Recognition',
};
---

<Layout metadata={metadata}>
  <!-- Content Widget **************** -->
  <Content
    title="High Achieiving Students"
    subtitle="This page showcases the high achieving students who have passed through Thoth Tech and made valuable and lasting contributions in their various teams and company as a whole."
  >
    <Fragment slot="bg">
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-[url('/src/assets/images/celebration.png')]"></div>
    </Fragment>
  </Content>

  <Content
    isReversed
    image={{
      src: '/Chloe-hulme.jpg',
      alt: 'Colorful Image',
      width: '1000',
      height: '1000',
    }}
  >
    <Fragment slot="content">
      <strong>Alumni: Chloe Hulme</strong><br />
      <br />
       During Chloe's time at Thoth Tech she led and contributed to the Art Gallery product. She successfully Dockerised
      the database, backend and frontend components, facilitating communication between components via a bridge network.
      She also led the restructuring of the repository in GitHub, adding in a CI workflow with compile and other tests.
      She wrote all the documentation present in the main code repo, as well as helped with some Deployment strategy
      documentation. <br />
      <br />
       Finally, She converted the backend to be fully asynchronous, migrated the backend framework to .NET 8.1, and made
      some frontend contributions; such as building the gallery view component and lightbox.<br />
      <br />
      <Button variant="secondary" href="https://github.com/chloeehulme" target="_blank">GitHub</Button>
      <Button variant="primary" href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/chloe-hulme/" target="_blank">
        LinkedIn
      </Button>
    </Fragment>

    <Fragment slot="bg">
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-white-50 dark:bg-transparent"></div>
    </Fragment>
  </Content>

  <Content
    image={{
      src: '/user1.png',
      alt: 'Colorful Image',
      width: '1000',
      height: '1000',
    }}
  >
    <Fragment slot="content">
      <strong>Alumni: Daniel Maddern</strong><br />
      <br />
       Graduating from Deakin University with a Bachelor of Computer Science, Daniel achieved a WAM of 93, securing High
      Distinctions in all subjects and reflecting his strong academic prowess. His engagement with Thoth Tech was
      instrumental in enhancing his professional skill set and preparing him for work post-university. Serving as a
      product lead for both Ontrack and the Art Gallery projects, and mentoring other senior students, he not only
      deepened his experience in Rails and Angular but also honed his leadership skills. His most significant technical
      contribution was the design and integration of a new feature for Ontrack, enabling seamless integration of Numbas
      testing within the system.<br />
      <br />
       In an effort to foster teamwork and connectivity, He spearheaded a company-wide team-building session at Thoth
      Tech to help students connect beyond their immediate teams, thereby promoting a cohesive and collaborative
      environment.<br />
      <br />
      <Button variant="secondary" href="https://github.com/maddernd?tab=repositories" target="_blank">GitHub</Button>
      <Button variant="primary" href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/daniel-maddern-90033533/" target="_blank">
        LinkedIn
      </Button>
    </Fragment>

    <Fragment slot="bg">
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-white-50 dark:bg-transparent"></div>
    </Fragment>
  </Content>

  <Content
    isReversed
    image={{
      src: '/user1.png',
      alt: 'Colorful Image',
      width: '1000',
      height: '1000',
    }}
  >
    <Fragment slot="content">
      <strong>Alumni: Student B</strong><br />
      <br />
